cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CR

This paper is likely to belong to the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with the explainability of neural networks and their decision boundaries. It also involves the study of the inductive bias of deep learning models. 

It could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as the study involves the analysis of the features of the dataset and their influence on the decision boundaries of deep models. 

Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves the development of a better understanding of the successes and limitations of deep learning. 

The paper also involves the study of adversarial robustness, which could place it under the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
